05248nam a22008775i 9783110899641DE-B159720220629043637.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||220629t20122004gw     fo  d z      eng d  a97831108996417 a10.1515/97831108996412doi  a(DE-B1597)56370  a(OCoLC)979907328  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 4aBS580.M3bS73 2004eb 7aREL0060902bisacsh04a296.4/92222  aBC 69802rvk0(DE-625)rvk/9612:1 aStavrakopoulou, Francesca, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aKing Manasseh and Child Sacrifice :bBiblical Distortions of Historical Realities /cFrancesca Stavrakopoulou.  aReprint 2012 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter, c[2012] 4c©2004  a1 online resource (405 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aBeihefte zur Zeitschrift für die alttestamentliche Wissenschaft ,x0934-2575 ;v338  aDissertationcOxford University (UK)d2003.00tFrontmatter -- tAcknowledgments -- tContents -- tAbbreviations -- tIntroduction -- t1 The Biblical Manasseh -- t2 The Historical Manasseh -- t3 The Distortion of Manasseh -- t4 The Biblical Portrayal of Child Sacrifice -- t5 The Historical Reality of Child Sacrifice -- tThe Distortion of Child Sacrifice -- tConclusions -- tBibliography -- tIndexes0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aDie hebräische Bibel stellt den König Manasse als die verabscheuungswürdigste Person und das Opfern von Kindern als die anstößigste Praxis innerhalb der Geschichte "Israels" dar. Die Autorin vertritt die These, dass geschichtlich gesehen weder die Person des Königs noch das Opfer so abwegig ist, wie es die hebräische Bibel zu behaupten scheint. Durch sorgfältige historische Rekonstruktion wird dargelegt, dass Manasse zu den erfolgreichsten judäischen Monarchen gehörte, und dass das Kindesopfer eine zentrale Rolle in den alten judäischen Riten spielte. Von ideologischen Interessen geleitet, hätten die biblischen Autoren daher die Wahrheit über Manasse und das Kindesopfer absichtlich verzerrt.  aThe Hebrew Bible portrays King Manasseh and child sacrifice as the most reprehensible person and the most objectionable practice within the story of 'Israel'. This monograph suggests that historically, neither were as deviant as the Hebrew Bible appears to insist. Through careful historical reconstruction, it is argued that Manasseh was one of Judah's most successful monarchs, and child sacrifice played a central role in ancient Judahite religious practice. The biblical writers, motivated by ideological concerns, have thus deliberately distorted the truth about Manasseh and child sacrifice.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aChild sacrifice in the Bible. 0aChild sacrificexJudaism. 4aAltes Testament. 4aManasseh. 4aMenschenopfer. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / Old Testament.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Theology and Religious Studies 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023854908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Theology and Religious Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110638165oZDB-23-GTR08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-DITION 2: BEST OF THEOLOGY TITLES IN ENGLISHz9783110305630oZDB-23-DBL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-DITION 2: BEST OF THEOLOGYz9783110305654oZDB-23-DBK0 cprintz978311017994140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311089964140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110899641423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110899641/original  a978-3-11-023854-9  DGBA Backlist Theology and Religious Studies 2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  